 You have a five quart jug and a three quart jug, and an unlimited supply of water
(but no measuring cups). How would you come up with exactly four quarts of water?
NOTE: The jugs are oddly shaped, such that flling up exactly ‘half’ of the jug would
be impossible

fill 5qt
poor until 3qt is full
empty 3qt
pour remaining 2 into 3qt
fill 5qt
fill 3qt until full
4 left
